Subject: Re: [T2] Continuing saga of 72 Bus Issues

Mike "Gamera" B wrote:
>I did a compression test today and found #1 & 2 cyl were (-at-)80 lbs. #3 & 4 were
>85 & 50 lbs. So I am thinking its time for new heads & perhaps cyl.

	That conclusion would follow only if the compressions were 
read with the motor warmed up, and throttle wide open.  Failing those 
conditions, you can get readings as low as 50 merely because the 
rings weren't sealed properly with oil &/or the cylinders weren't 
taking in a full charge of air.

